🎯Revising OOPS
    👉OOPS: OOP stands for Object Oriented Programming,
        which is a type of computer programming that is based on the CONCEPT of objects.

    ▶️Classes :User-defined data types that act as blueprints for objects.
        Classes define the structure and behavior of an object, including its attributes, methods, and objects.
    ▶️Objects :Instances of a class that are created with specific data.
        Objects can represent real-world objects or abstract entities.
    ▶️Constructor : Constructor is a special function inside a class which have same name
        of the class and is use to initialize the values of member fields.
    ▶️This keyword : Use to refer the current invoking object.
